==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Curette
<hw>Cu*rette"</hw> <pr>(k⟦usdot⟧*r⟦ecr⟧t")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>curer</ets> to cleanse.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A scoop or ring with either a blunt or a cutting edge, for removing
substances from the walls of a cavity, as from the eye, ear, or
womb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curette</ent>⟦br⟧

